parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive belt can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, and can also cause the power steering and air conditioning systems to malfunction, which can lead to a loss of vehicle control and increase the risk of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, leading to environmental harm and potential health risks, and can also cause the engine to run poorly, leading to decreased fuel efficiency and performance.

the engine runs poorly or stalls
the catalytic converter is clogged or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the muffler can cause the vehicle to emit excessive noise, leading to a disturbance to the peace and potential hearing damage, and can also cause the exhaust system to malfunction, leading to decreased fuel efficiency and performance.

vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the doors to become stuck in the locked or unlocked position, potentially trapping occupants inside the vehicle or allowing unauthorized access, which can compromise safety and security.
symptoms: The passenger side front or rear door locks fail to operate
the doors are stuck in the locked or unlocked position
the door locks make a clicking or grinding noise
the door locks are slow to respond or do not respond at all.
